Actually, the hint says: "The render options expose `serverData` (including `serverData.requestHeaders` and `serverData.locale`), which you can use to compute `data-theme` and `lang` before rendering."

So in `entry.ssr.tsx`, I'll read the cookie from `serverData.requestHeaders` (the `cookie` header), parse it, resolve theme and locale, and set `containerAttributes` accordingly. Also use `serverData.locale` which was set by the middleware via `event.locale()`.

